SIMPLE: fuming
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fuming
<hw>Fum"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Producing fumes, or
vapors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cadet's fuming liquid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>alkarsin.</cd> -- <col><b>Fuming liquor of Libavius</b></col>
<fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>, <cd>stannic chloride; the chloride of tin,
<chform>SnCl4</chform>, forming a colorless, mobile liquid which fumes
in the air. Mixed with water it solidifies to the so-called <xex>butter
of tin</xex>.</cd> -- <col><b>Fuming sulphuric acid</b></col>.
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <cd>Same as <cref>Disulphuric acid</cref>, uder
<er>Disulphuric</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fumingly</ent>⟦br⟧
